# Increase Header Vertical Size in PDF

The goal is to increase the height of the header section in the leave request PDF generator (`corporatePdf.ts`). This will shift the content sections downwards, reducing the large amount of empty space current present below Section 4 (Contact & Handover) on the first page.

## Proposed Changes

### PDF Library

#### [MODIFY] [corporatePdf.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/lib/corporatePdf.ts)

- Increase the spacing before the thick black separator in `drawHeader`.
- Increase the return value of `drawHeader` to provide more padding before the first content section.

## Open Questions

- Should I also increase the spacing between the sections (1, 2, 3, 4) slightly to further distribute the content across the page?

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Generate a Leave Request PDF and visually inspect the vertical alignment.
- Verify that "4. CONTACT & HANDOVER" is still comfortably within the first page.
